commit.message:
Migrate CI to GitHub Actions

Now that Travis CI.org is no more, this PR migrates the CI to GitHub actions.

In addition to setting up the pipeline, this PR:

1. Removes several gems that are either inapplicable or unsupported (wwtd, minitest-rg)
2. Updates the gemspec and Gemfile to use the gemspec for specifying dependencies
3. Eliminates use of an unused loop variable in favor of an explicit power.
4. Adds testing on modern Rubies
5. Removes the Gemfile.lock so that different Rubies can use different minitest/rake versions

Add support for detection of UTF-7

commit.message:
Add support for detection of UTF-7

- [x] Aids in the ability of Ruby programs to handle UTF-7, real or fake, appropriately, for example: https://geldgokken.info
- [x] Adds new spec for UTF-7 detection
- [x] Included UTF-7 file for the test suite is a converted UTF-8 file from a reference set of UTF charset files.
  - Original is at https://raw.githubusercontent.com/QbProg/unicode-samples/master/unicat/files/utf7.txt
  - It can be read as ASCII-8BIT with `a = File.open("test/simple_assets/UTF-7.txt", "r:BINARY") { |f| f.read }`
